      "content": "- **Structural alerts relevant to CYP2D6 inhibition**\n  - Classic CYP2D6 inhibitors commonly feature a **protonatable basic nitrogen** (often tertiary amine) + **aromatic/lipophilic region** (\u201cquinidine-like\u201d pharmacophore).\n  - This molecule has the lipophilic/aromatic region, but **lacks a clear strongly protonatable amine**.",
