      "content": "## 5) Verification / uncertainty check\n- **Potential counterpoint:** Some heteroaromatic N-rich systems can still coordinate/position near the heme and inhibit P450s without a cationic amine, especially if very lipophilic. The bis-CF\u2083 phenyl boosts this possibility.\n- **Why still negative overall:** CYP2D6 inhibition correlates particularly strongly with **protonatable amines**; this scaffold appears **neutral/weakly basic** at pH 7.4, making strong CYP2D6 inhibition less likely than for enzymes where hydrophobic binding dominates.\n- Uncertainty remains because actual pKa of the fused heteroaromatic nitrogens and the 3D conformation could increase binding more than expected.",
